{{> header}}
<h1>Diglias GO node.js sample application</h1>
<h2>Authenticate</h2>
<p>When authenticating users as set of attributes will be requested from the user trough the Diglias app. By default the
    attribute set to request is part of the configuration. Using EAPI is is possible to limit the requested
    attributes to a subset of the configured attributes.</p>
<form method="post" action="/authenticate">
    <h3>Select attributes to request</h3>
    <p><input type="checkbox" name="givenname">Given name ( <code>givenname</code> )</p>
    <p><input type="checkbox" name="sn">Sir Name ( <code>sn</code> )</p>
    <p><input type="checkbox" name="mobile">Mobile phone ( <code>mobile</code> )</p>
    <p><input type="checkbox" name="email">E-mail adress ( <code>email</code> )</p>
    <p><em>If none checked, default configuratuion will be used.</em></p>
    <input type="submit" value="Authenticate" class="dButton">
</form>
{{> footer}}
